node.title: Roots
node.description: Sunset over Little Lagoon just before Thanksgiving.  I thought these old pine roots provided an interesting foreground.  Please view on black.

node.title: Ginkgo of Glenwood
node.description: Edited in Lightroom with the Selective Adjustment brush at -100 saturation for all but the leaves.  A little tedious but puts the focus on the tree instead of the stop sign.

node.title: Elk Silhouettes
node.description: Silhouette of a young bull and cows early one morning in the Cataloochee Valley.

node.title: Longleaf Sunset
node.description: Went up to the Moorman Mountain Overlook for sunset on Sunday afternoon.  Although this faces East, there was some nice reflected light and a better view of the valley.  Please view on black.

node.title: A Safe Place
node.description: A mother elk feeds her calf early one morning in the Cataloochee Valley.

node.title: Leader of the Bugle Corps
node.description: One of the many elk we saw on a recent trip to Cataloochee.  We were a little late for the rut, but we still found a bugler in the fog early in the morning.

node.title: Autumn Road
node.description: Cataloochee Loop in the fog.  Please view on black.

node.title: Painted Pink
node.description: Took my almost two-year old daughter out to Hillabee to see the sunset a few weeks back.  She enjoyed picking up rocks and we were treated to a great view.

node.title: Oconaluftee Gold (wide view)
node.description: Wide view of the Oconaluftee River and fall color near Cherokee, NC.  Waders were a must for this shot.
